## Static observations

- DESIGN resource-limit table states maximum expansion is `32768` and single-layer maximum data size is `2 GB`: `modules/gemini-bloom/DESIGN.md:552-559`.
- Command/config paths enforce expansion upper bounds: `modules/gemini-bloom/src/bloom_commands.cc:133-137`, `modules/gemini-bloom/src/bloom_commands.cc:300-304`, `modules/gemini-bloom/src/bloom_config.cc:44-50`.
- RDB/wire deserialization paths reject zero expansion but do not enforce `kMaxExpansion`: `modules/gemini-bloom/src/bloom_rdb.cc:180-189`, `modules/gemini-bloom/src/bloom_rdb.cc:281-305`.
- `BloomLayer::Create` enforces a local 2GB per-layer data-size cap: `modules/gemini-bloom/src/bloom_filter.cc:123-131`.
- `ValidateLayerFields` does not enforce the same 2GB per-layer data-size cap for RDB/wire fields: `modules/gemini-bloom/src/bloom_rdb.cc:53-68`.
- RDB/wire deserialization enforces only total data-size cap before allocation: `modules/gemini-bloom/src/bloom_rdb.cc:203-209`, `modules/gemini-bloom/src/bloom_rdb.cc:295-297`.
- Tests cover expansion command overflow and total wire data-size over 4GB, but do not cover RDB/wire expansion over 32768 or per-layer data-size over 2GB while total data-size remains <=4GB: `modules/gemini-bloom/tests/tcl/bloom_test.tcl:1015-1023`, `modules/gemini-bloom/tests/tcl/bloom_test.tcl:1226-1246`, `modules/gemini-bloom/tests/bloom_rdb_test.cc:1054-1074`, `modules/gemini-bloom/tests/bloom_rdb_test.cc:1251-1265`, `modules/gemini-bloom/tests/bloom_rdb_test.cc:1306-1326`.
